OL,6,FBut just an hour later, the defendant
OL,7,Fbroke into a 75-year-old woman's home
OL,8,Fto steal cash, earrings and he later
OL,9,Fused her bank card to buy items from
OL,10,Fconvenience stores.
OL,12,FFour days earlier, Laughton tried to
OL,13,Fpersuade a "frail" 84-year-old woman,
OL,14,Fwho had a history of heart failure and
OL,15,Flimited mobility, that he was a
OL,16,Fpoliceman before going through the
OL,17,Faddress looking for items to steal.
