OL,6,FAnother break-in saw Laughton claiming
OL,7,Fto be delivering parcels when he
OL,8,Fentered the home of an elderly woman
OL,9,Fwith mobility issues, and stole two
OL,10,Fgold watches, one belonging to her
OL,11,F"much-loved and lamented late
OL,12,Fhusband," the other given as an
OL,13,Fanniversary gift and both of immense
OL,14,Fsentimental value.
OL,16,FOn March 3, he entered a 59-year-old
OL,17,Fman's flat in Hucknall, but his would-
OL,18,Fbe victim became suspicious and
OL,19,FLaughton fled.
